As Diamante Net evolves, DCP drives innovation and sustainability, shaping the future of blockchain technology beyond traditional methods. 🚀💡 #BlockchainInnovation

Nomination & Ballot Protocols:

-> Nomination: Selects which transactions enter the ledger.
-> Ballot: Confirms and secures these transactions, ensuring ledger integrity. 🗂️📜 #ContributorNetwork.

-> Ultra-fast transactional speed, reaching consensus in less than 3 seconds.😁

-> Handles an average of 7500 transactions per second and 10 million daily transactions with a minimal infrastructure requirement.😎 #GUILD #DIAM

Diamante’s anti-spamming controls are a formidable barrier against malicious elements. By implementing advanced algorithms and real-time monitoring systems, the Diamante Network effectively filters out spam transactions, safeguarding its integrity and performance.🌟🔗 https://t.co/l3WxzCl7R7

Key Components:

1. Quorum Set: Trusted nodes for decision-making.
2. Thresholds & Quorum Slices: Minimum votes needed for consensus.
3. Node Blocking Sets: Can disrupt consensus.
4. Quorum: Nodes needed to finalize decisions.
5. Statement: Nodes' opinions on transactions. 📊🔍 https://t.co/gvOv7ClNzb

Unlike traditional methods like PoW or PoS, Diamante Net’s DCP focuses on trust among nodes instead of heavy computing or stake ownership. This opens up network control to anyone. 🔐⚖️#GUILD #DIAM https://t.co/XggfnWAEIc

Diamante Net is the most efficient option on the list. The network maximizes transaction processing speeds by reducing latency through FHE-based encryption. As a result, the Diamante network can handle large volume of transactions without compromising security or functionality.🤝 https://t.co/xfA0FUfa1e

DCP is the backbone of our decentralized payment system, ensuring nodes agree on transactions without relying on a central authority. It’s about trust and reliability, not just computing power. 🛡️⚙️ https://t.co/Rfz4KcDJkR
Ever wondered how Diamante Net secures transactions? Let’s explore our unique Consensus Protocol (DCP). @diam_stack @DIAM_Guild https://t.co/uSs1SPJkvc

Transaction Fee Minimum

Avocado has a minimum transaction fee of $0.01 USD on most networks. If a transaction fee were to be below $0.01 USD the fee will on Avocado will be $0.01.*

*Fuse Network transactions have a fee minimum of $0.001

Here's how it's calculated:

Transaction Price  = $ value of the gas spent in native token + 20% markup  For example: a 10 cent transaction will cost 12 cents on Avocado.

Gas Upcharge

There is a 20% markup that is charged on transactions on any network when using Avocado. Half of this fee is shared with integrators and all transactions are deducted in USDC.

No Frontend Charges

There are no additional fees from Avocado when using bridges, DEXes or other operations through the frontend.

Fees on Avocado

All transactions on Avocado carry a fee in the form of a gas upcharge. This fee helps maintain the relayer network and is shared with DApp integrations.
